&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kairos Power is a new nuclear energy technology and engineering company whose mission is to enable the world’s transition to clean energy, with the ultimate goal to dramatically improve people’s quality of life while protecting the environment. This goal will be accomplished through the commercialization of the fluoride-salt-cooled, high-temperature reactor (FHR) that can be deployed with robust safety, affordable costs, and flexible operation to accommodate the expansion of variable renewables.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kairos Power is seeking a highly motivated fabricator with expertise relevant to fabrication of piping systems. In this role you will contribute to successful completion of piping systems for the various systems of our reactors. This role requires in position and out of position welding. You will be responsible for meeting timelines and increased improvement of the pipe welding capabilities. This includes manual tig welding as well as orbital welding. The candidate must have knowledge of infrastructure, setup, operation, and maintenance requirement for advanced shop equipment. Candidate shall have knowledge of modern fabrication techniques, and proven record of successful cross-functional collaboration. Candidate ideally takes pride in their craftsmanship, organization, and attention to detail. We offer a fast moving and exciting environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fabricate and assemble piping systems to meet engineering and print specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform high-quality TIG and orbital welding on a variety of materials and pipe schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret and work from isometric drawings, blueprints, and technical specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide fast turn-around prototypes for engineering development and testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Engineering teams to problem solve fabrication issues and execute work request.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propose optimal/innovative fabrication techniques for given jobs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate as a team member on large-scale fabrication projects, ensuring timelines and quality standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fabricate piping systems to meet print requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct training occasionally on machine capability and best practices to enhance fabrication of piping systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain current welding certifications and documentation in accordance to company and ASME standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all work complies with applicable safety standards, procedures, and codes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain equipment, tools, and the fabrication workspace in safe and reliable condition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED and 3+ years related experience and/or training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years working in a fabrication/welding shop desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GTAW experience involving variety of materials including tubing to schedule 160 pipe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to pass 6G super coupon weld certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with manual tools required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Manual machining (Lathe and Mill) desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with 3D CAD software desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Stainless material and vessel fabrication desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge, Skills &amp;amp; Abilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and understand isomet

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kairos Power is a new nuclear energy technology and engineering company whose mission is to enable the world’s transition to clean energy, with the ultimate goal to dramatically improve people’s quality of life while protecting the environment. This goal will be accomplished through the commercialization of the fluoride-salt-cooled, high-temperature reactor (FHR) that can be deployed with robust safety, affordable costs, and flexible operation to accommodate the expansion of variable renewables.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kairos Power, is a new nuclear energy technology and engineering company whose mission is to enable the world’s transition to clean energy, with the ultimate goal to dramatically improve people’s quality of life while protecting the environment. This goal will be accomplished through the commercialization of the fluoride-salt-cooled, high-temperature reactor (FHR) that can be deployed with robust safety, affordable costs, and flexible operation to accommodate the expansion of variable renewables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kairos Power is seeking a Facilities Mechanical Technician with broad building and mechanical expertise supporting industrial, commercial and/or R&amp;amp;D facilities. This position will be located at the Kairos Power Southwest facility in Albuquerque, New Mexico and will report to the Facilities Department. The Facilities Maintenance Technician will support a variety of facilities maintenance tasks across the site including performing inspections, installations, repairs, replacements, and other general tasks on existing facility infrastructure. The role will also conduct testing, operations, troubleshooting, and mechanical work in support of the engineering teams onsite. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience performing/coordinating maintenance on boilers, chillers, and HVAC systems and experience working with R&amp;amp;D test equipment, manufacturing equipment, and other commercial building systems including Building Management Systems (BMS), fire protection, fire alarms, access control, security cameras, and security alarms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical support for required mechanical tasks in collaboration with internal facilities, construction, engineering and project teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete preventative and corrective maintenance/troubleshooting on site Boilers, Chillers, HVAC, and other mechanical systems (plumbing, compressed air, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the scope and coordination with facilities contractors to complete required projects/work on site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a detailed understanding and knowledge of the building’s mechanical, electrical, and plumbing systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the construction and operations of Boilers, Chillers, HVAC and other building systems equipment in support of R&amp;amp;D testing at the facility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of operating standards and Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for mechanical equipment (Boilers, Chillers, Reverse Osmosis (RO), HVAC, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform lockout/tagout to isolate components and de-energize equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
